What's built
Backend (4 migrations + 4 models + 1 service + 1 controller + 1 mailable + 1 email template):

Catalog stored in voucher_products, codes encrypted in voucher_codes
Full order lifecycle: validate → reserve → deduct balance → build Excel in memory → email → mark sent → no file on disk
Low stock warnings at configurable threshold per product

Frontend (3 views + store + API client + router):

/vouchers — Card grid catalog, search, filter, pagination, quick-add per denomination, detail modal with T&C
/vouchers/send — Customer search, SPOC auto-select (or pick if multiple), live balance check
/vouchers/confirm — Full order summary, sends on confirm, success overlay


Install instructions
1. Install PhpSpreadsheet (needed for Excel generation):
bashcd ~/avirqo-backend
composer require phpoffice/phpspreadsheet
2. Copy backend files:
bashSRC=~/Downloads/avirqo-vouchers

cp "$SRC/backend/database/migrations/"*.php ~/avirqo-backend/database/migrations/
cp "$SRC/backend/app/Models/"*.php ~/avirqo-backend/app/Models/
cp -R "$SRC/backend/app/Services/Vouchers" ~/avirqo-backend/app/Services/
mkdir -p ~/avirqo-backend/app/Http/Controllers/Api/Vouchers
cp "$SRC/backend/app/Http/Controllers/Api/Vouchers/"*.php ~/avirqo-backend/app/Http/Controllers/Api/Vouchers/
cp "$SRC/backend/app/Mail/VoucherOrderMail.php" ~/avirqo-backend/app/Mail/
cp "$SRC/backend/resources/views/emails/voucher-order.blade.php" ~/avirqo-backend/resources/views/emails/
cp "$SRC/backend/routes/modules/vouchers.php" ~/avirqo-backend/routes/modules/
3. Register voucher routes in routes/api.php:
bashecho "require __DIR__.'/modules/vouchers.php';" >> ~/avirqo-backend/routes/api.php
4. Run migrations:
bashphp artisan migrate
5. Copy frontend files:
bashcp -R "$SRC/frontend/src/modules/vouchers" ~/avirqo-frontend/src/modules/
6. Add voucher routes to main router — open ~/avirqo-frontend/src/router/index.js and add:
jsimport voucherRoutes from '../modules/vouchers/router';
// inside routes array:
...voucherRoutes,
7. Update the sidebar in AppLayout.vue — the Vouchers link is already an <a> placeholder, change it to a RouterLink:
html<RouterLink class="avq-nav-item" to="/vouchers" active-class="active">
  <span class="avq-nav-icon">🎁</span> Vouchers
</RouterLink>
8. Rebuild frontend:
bashcd ~/avirqo-frontend && npm run build
One important note — the catalog will show "No vouchers imported yet" until you import products from Xoxoday and insert codes into voucher_products and voucher_codes. The import mechanism (Fetch from Xoxoday) is a separate integration — let me know when you're ready to build that and I'll wire up the Xoxoday API.